R and R1 each are independently hydrogen or methyl;


R2, R3 and R4 each are independently hydrogen, halogen, nitro or trifluoromethyl, provided R2, R3, and R4 are not all hydrogen;


R5 is bromo, chloro or nitro;


R6 is hydrogen or fluoro;


n is an integer from 0 to 6;


m is an integer of 0 or 1; and


R7 is CH3, --CRR1 OH, --CHO, --C.dbd.NOH, --COCH3 or aryl optionally substituted by one or two substituents selected from the group consisting of halogen, hydroxy, methoxy, amino, acetylamino and trifluoromethyl;

To a solution of the ester prepared in Example 5 in ethanol and anhydrous HCl in a Parr shaker bottle, PtO2 (5-10% by weight) was treated under nitrogen.


The resultant suspension was hydrogenated at 60 psi overnight.


The catalyst was filtered off and the filtrate was rotary evaporated to afford the title compound: mp 193-195 (degree)  C.;
